The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, December 07, 2003  Metro Briefs
																																																		Burglars  broke open the shutters of a jewellery shop on Central Garden  Reach Road in the Watgunge police station area on Saturday  morning and made off with jewellery worth around Rs 15 lakh.  reliminary investigations revealed that a gas lighter was  used to bore into the metal shutters. The hole was large  enough for a man to pass through. According to the owner,  all gold and gold-plated ornaments were stolen, said an officer  of Watgunge police station. Police hinted at the role of an  insider in the robbery. The burglary wing of the detective  department has been informed of the incident. 																																																		A  house on Prince Anwar Shah Road caught fire on Saturday and  five fire tenders were pressed into service to douse the flames.  Another fire broke out on Topsia Road where some tyres had  been dumped. Firemen doused the flames in half an hour. 																																																		Chief  minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjees mother, Leela Bhattacharjee,  78, was admitted to Woodburn ward of SSKM Hospital on Saturday  afternoon. Doctors said she was suffering from a respiratory  problem. She was in a stable condition till reports last came  in. 

